statement:
\emph{This problem contains three numerical series. For each of them,
find out whether it converges or diverges. You should provide
appropriate justification in order to receive credit.}

\begin{align*}\sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{2^k(k!)^2}{(2k)!}\end{align*}

Recall that $k! = 1\cdot2\cdot3\cdot \ldots \cdot k$.
